$IREN IREN Limited: Technical read

Price action
After the strong rally into the 60+ area, $IREN corrected sharply and is now trading in a sideways range around 40–45. The stock looks to be building a base rather than continuing the downtrend, but upside confirmation is still missing.

Key levels

Support
•40–41 – Current consolidation floor where buyers keep stepping in
•36–38 – Panic flush zone from the recent selloff, strong reaction level
•32–34 – Major structural support from the prior base

Resistance
•45–47 – Immediate supply zone and range top (needs reclaim for momentum)
•52–55 – Prior distribution area before the breakdown
•60–63 – Major resistance from the last peak

RSI
RSI around 45 suggests neutral-to-weak conditions. Momentum is stabilizing but not yet bullish. A move back above 50 RSI would confirm strengthening buyers.

What the tape is saying
This looks like a base-building phase after a sharp correction. Volatility compressed and price is holding support, which is constructive. A breakout above 45–47 would likely start the next trend leg, while losing 40 would reopen downside.

My estimate (opinion)
Neutral-to-bullish. The structure looks constructive and similar to an accumulation range. Odds favor a move toward 50+ if 45–47 breaks cleanly.

$ASTS AST SpaceMobile: Intraday read

Momentum
Momentum is muted after a sharp selloff from the highs. The tape is trying to stabilize, but buyers haven’t proven a clean reversal yet.

Structure
Lower highs and lower lows since the peak, now compressing in a tight range around the mid-80s. This is “base building” behavior: it can resolve higher, but it needs a reclaim to flip trend back up.

RSI
RSI is in the low-40s (weak). That usually signals sellers still have control unless RSI can reclaim and hold the 50 line on the next push.

Key levels (Support / Resistance)
Support
•82–85: current balance zone (where price is being accepted right now)
•78–80: prior reaction area, likely dip-buy defense on any flush
•70–72: bigger pivot support, losing this would confirm broader weakness

Resistance
•88–90: first reclaim area (where sellers have been leaning)
•95–100: prior breakdown zone, needs to flip to support to restart upside
•105–110: overhead supply from the prior range, next magnet if trend flips

Read-through (trigger + invalidation)
•Trigger: reclaim 88–90 and then hold 85+ on a pullback (turns the range into a base)
•Invalidation: lose 78–80 with follow-through (signals the base failed and downside is back in play)

$PBR Petrobras: Intraday read

Momentum
Clean momentum bid. Price is pressing fresh highs with shallow pullbacks, suggesting dip-buyers are in control.

Structure
Uptrend sequence intact (higher highs, higher lows). The recent pause around 15.0–15.5 acted like a tight base, and the breakout is now being confirmed above ~16.

RSI
RSI is elevated (near the 70 zone), which usually means strong trend not “must sell” by itself. Watch for bullish RSI holding above 50 on pullbacks.

Key levels (Support / Resistance)
Support
•15.80–16.00: breakout zone, first spot bulls want to defend (turns prior resistance into support)
•15.20–15.40: prior consolidation shelf, “last good” support for this leg
•14.80–15.00: trend pivot, lose this and the move turns into a range again

Resistance
•16.30–16.50: current extension zone, first area where profit-taking can show up
•16.80–17.20: next upside magnet if the breakout holds
•18.00: psychological round-number target if oil tailwinds stay hot

Read-through (trigger + invalidation)
•Trigger: hold above 16.00 and push through 16.50 for continuation
•Invalidation: sustained trade back below 15.20 shifts this from “trend” to “chop/mean reversion”

Macro note
$PBR is a top pick as long as tensions between the US and Iran keep rising, because the tape tends to reward oil-linked cash flow when geopolitical risk lifts crude.

$BTC Bitcoin: Technical read

Price action
Strong breakdown from the ~95k area followed by a sharp flush toward ~60k. Since then, price is stabilizing in a tight range around 65k–70k, suggesting a pause after heavy distribution rather than a confirmed reversal.

Key levels

Support
•64k–66k – Current range floor and short-term demand zone (buyers repeatedly step in here)
•60k–62k – Capitulation low area (last strong reaction zone)
•55k–57k – Major structural support if the range breaks down

Resistance
•70k–72k – Range ceiling and first reclaim level (needs to break for momentum shift)
•78k–80k – Prior breakdown zone where sellers accelerated
•88k–92k – Major distribution area from the previous top structure

RSI
RSI ~34–35, still in a weak regime but stabilizing. Momentum is no longer collapsing, which often precedes a base phase.

What the tape is saying
This looks like a post-liquidation consolidation. Sellers pushed hard but are losing urgency. Bulls need a clean break above 72k to signal a meaningful reversal attempt. Until then, this is a range market inside a larger downtrend.

My estimate (opinion)
Most likely scenario is sideways between 64k–72k before the next big move. A reclaim of 72k would likely trigger a fast move toward 80k, while losing 64k would probably send price back to the 60k region.

Support

•75–77: prior breakdown area (lose this and downside opens fast)
•68–70: bigger pivot support (last “major” floor from prior structure)

Resistance
•88–90: first reclaim zone (needs to flip to support to change character)
•98–102: prior breakdown shelf (where sellers previously leaned)
•110–115: supply from the distribution zone (harder cap unless momentum returns)

Read-through (trigger + invalidation)
•Trigger: reclaim 88–90 and hold -> opens 98–102, then 110–115 if momentum follows
•Invalidation: lose 80 -> likely tests 75–77; lose that and 68–70 becomes the magnet

Momentum
Strong bid today. Clean push off the recent low with expanding green candles - buyers are in control.

Structure
This looks like a sharp V-reversal into a reclaim attempt. Price has reclaimed the prior range top near the 100 area and is pressing toward the next supply zone.

RSI
RSI ~61 with RSI MA ~48: momentum is back above neutral and accelerating. That usually supports follow-through as long as RSI stays >50.

Key levels (Support/Resistance)
Support
•100–102: reclaim shelf (former resistance turning into demand)
•94–96: mid-range pivot (where failed bounces previously rolled)

Resistance
•106–108: current overhead supply (local ceiling from prior pivots)
•112–115: next range cap (where sellers previously defended)
•120–125: major supply zone (top of the broader chop area)

Read-through (trigger + invalidation)

•Invalidation: lose 100 -> likely mean-revert to 94–96; lose that and the reversal weakens fast

Tape note
In a generally difficult tape today, $NBIS is acting strong - relative demand is showing up when many names are struggling, which is exactly what you want to see.

Momentum
Trend is still up. After the strong impulse leg, price is digesting near highs and holding gains - that’s typically constructive, not distributive.

Structure
Base -> breakout -> vertical push -> tight flag just under prior highs. This is the kind of structure that can resolve higher if crude catches a bid.

RSI
RSI ~68 with RSI MA ~71: still elevated (momentum strong), but no longer accelerating. Expect chop unless price reclaims the highs cleanly.

Support
•15.0–15.2: flag support, where dips have been bought (first demand zone)
•14.3–14.6: breakout retest zone (if this holds, trend stays intact)

Resistance
•15.9–16.1: local ceiling (needs a clean break to trigger continuation)
•16.4–16.6: next supply/extension zone (post-breakout magnet)
•17.0+: psychological extension area if momentum ramps

•Trigger: break and hold above 16.1 -> opens 16.4–16.6, then 17+
•Invalidation: lose 15.0 -> likely drift to 14.3–14.6; lose that and the breakout is in question

Macro note
$PBR is a strong tactical pick if the Iran situation pushes crude higher - oil strength tends to show up fast in cash-flowing producers, and this chart already looks “ready” (tight consolidation under highs).

RSI

$PLTR – Palantir Technologies: Intraday read

Momentum
Short-term momentum is still pressured after a sharp downside impulse, but selling velocity is slowing. The last few candles show reduced range and early stabilization.

Structure
Clear lower-high / lower-low sequence from the recent peak. Price is now consolidating near the prior demand zone, shifting from trend to range behavior intraday.

RSI
RSI is deeply oversold and starting to flatten. This is not a buy signal by itself, but it suggests selling exhaustion rather than fresh downside acceleration.

Key levels
•Support: 128–130 (current base, must hold)
•Resistance: 136–138 (first supply / reclaim level)
•Upper resistance: 145–148 (trend repair zone)

Read-through
•Hold above 128–130 → scope for a mean-reversion push toward 136–138.
•Lose 128 on a closing basis → downside opens toward the low 120s.

This is a stabilization phase, not a confirmed reversal yet. Patience > prediction.

Seeing red → green transitions across multiple stocks is very encouraging.

This usually signals:
•Selling pressure getting absorbed
•Weak hands exiting, stronger hands stepping in
•Momentum stabilizing after a pullback
•The market rotating, not breaking

When many names flip red to green at the same time, it’s often a breadth tell, not a coincidence.

Early sign of risk appetite returning.
Now it’s about follow-through, not chasing.

$RKLB – Rocket Lab | Weekly quick take

Price action
•Strong impulsive uptrend from the lows, followed by a sharp pullback from the highs.
•Current move looks like a pullback within an uptrend, not a confirmed trend break.

Structure
•Higher highs and higher lows remain intact as long as price holds the mid-60s.
•Recent selling reads as profit-taking, not distribution.

RSI (weekly)
•RSI around 53–54 after cooling off from overbought levels.
•Healthy reset, no clear bearish HTF divergence.

Key levels
•Support: ~65–62 (structural higher low zone).
•Major support: ~55 (prior breakout base).
•Resistance: ~75–78 first, then prior highs ~95–100.

What the tape is saying
•Holding the 60s keeps the bullish structure alive and allows base-building for the next leg.
•Losing ~55 would shift the narrative to deeper consolidation/range.

My estimate (opinion)
•Base case: continued consolidation, and if 62–65 holds, a push toward 75–80 before any renewed attempt at the highs.
•This does not look like a top. It looks like a leader resetting after a strong move.

$EOSE Eos Energy Enterprises: Technical read

Price action
•Weekly trend turned into a sharp uptrend into the ~$18–$19 zone, then a hard reversal + distribution sequence.
•Price is now back near ~$11, which is the “make or break” area for whether this is a normal reset or a larger unwind.

Key levels
Support
•10.8–11.2: current pivot (last line before the prior breakout leg starts to unravel).
•9.4–9.8: next demand shelf (where the prior base/rotation likely sits).
•7.8–8.3: deeper structural support (if the unwind extends and the trend fully resets).

Resistance
•12.6–13.2: first supply zone (failed bounce area; needs reclaim to stabilize).
•14.8–15.5: breakdown level (reclaim would signal momentum is returning).
•17.5–19.0: prior top supply (major overhead, likely needs time to revisit).

RSI
•Weekly RSI is ~46 with RSI MA ~59: momentum has rolled over; bulls need time + basing to re-accelerate.

What the tape is saying
•Bulls want a weekly hold above ~11 and then a reclaim of ~13 to confirm “pullback, not breakdown.”
•Bears want weekly closes below ~10.8 to open the path toward ~9.5 and possibly ~8.

My estimate (opinion)
•Cautious here. I’d treat ~11 as the decision level: hold + base can set up a tradable rebound, but a clean break below it shifts the odds to a deeper reset toward 9–8.

$IREN IREN Limited: Technical read

Price action
•Weekly chart is in a post-parabolic digestion: peak in the ~$70s, sharp reset, now basing around the low-$40s.
•The last few candles look like stabilization, but price still needs a clean reclaim to flip momentum.

Key levels
Support
•40–42: current demand shelf (where buyers keep defending, losing it re-opens downside).
•34–36: prior reaction lows (next “must-hold” if $40 breaks).
•28–30: last major base area before the big run (deep support, likely where buyers get loud again).

Resistance
•45–48: first supply zone (recent breakdown area, needs reclaim to confirm strength).
•55–60: prior rebound cap (overhead supply from trapped sellers).
•70–75: cycle-high supply (major distribution zone, only relevant if trend fully re-accelerates).

RSI
•Weekly RSI is ~50: neutral. Not washed out, not trending strong.
•RSI staying above 50 supports a base-to-reclaim attempt; slipping under 50 keeps it range-bound to weak.

What the tape is saying
•This is range repair, not a breakout. Bulls need a reclaim of 45–48 to prove the base is real.
•Until then, the market is treating rallies as sellable bounces into overhead supply.

My estimate (opinion)
•Bias is neutral-to-slightly bullish as long as 40–42 holds, with 45–48 as the decision gate. I’d respect the base, but I’d pay up only after a weekly reclaim, not inside the chop.
